// No single-line code fix — this is an inherent limitation of
// needing a prior pivot to compare against.
// Awareness-only: the first zone on any chart or after clearing history
// will be graded one point lower than it might deserve.
// If sweep grades matter a lot, check whether the first zone's grade
// seems unusually low compared to surrounding context.

// Inside BOTH the supply and demand re-grade loops (two separate locations),
// replace the existing tr = ... line with a progressive version:

// OLD (supply loop example):
tr = math.max(0, math.min(95, zTransp - g * 7 + (dimTapped and array.get(supTouch, i) > 0 ? 14 : 0)))

// NEW (each tap adds 7 more transparency, capped at +28 total = 4 taps):
int taps = array.get(supTouch, i)
int tapDim = dimTapped ? math.min(28, taps * 7) : 0
tr = math.max(0, math.min(95, zTransp - g * 7 + tapDim))

